30 SECTION 7. IC 14-25-4.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
31 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
32 UPON PASSAGE]:
33 Chapter 4.5. Moratorium on New Major Ground Water
34 Withdrawal Facilities
35 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "county executive" means the
36 board of commissioners of a county elected under IC 36-2-2-2.
37 Sec. 2. As used in this chapter, "ground water withdrawal
38 facility" means a facility that meets all of the following conditions:
39 (1) The facility includes:
40 (A) one (1) well; or
41 (B) two (2) or more wells under common ownership or
42 control.
2026 IN 1379—LS 6276/DI 150

6
1 (2) The well or wells described in subdivision (1) have, in the
2 aggregate, from all sources and by all methods, the capability
3 of withdrawing not more than nine million nine hundred
4 ninety-nine thousand nine hundred ninety-nine (9,999,999)
5 gallons of ground water from one (1) or more aquifers in one
6 (1) day.
7 (3) Either:
8 (A) the facility is connected to existing pipeline facilities; or
9 (B) plans for the facility include the connection of the
10 facility to pipeline facilities;
11 through which not more than four million nine hundred
12 ninety-nine thousand nine hundred ninety-nine (4,999,999)
13 gallons of ground water withdrawn by the well or wells to
14 which subdivision (1) refers could be transported in one (1)
15 day to a destination located at least twenty (20) miles from the
16 well or wells.
17 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "major ground water withdrawal
18 facility" means a facility that meets all of the following conditions:
19 (1) The facility includes:
20 (A) one (1) well; or
21 (B) two (2) or more wells under common ownership or
22 control.
23 (2) The well or wells described in subdivision (1) have, in the
24 aggregate, from all sources and by all methods, the capability
25 of withdrawing at least ten million (10,000,000) gallons of
26 ground water from one (1) or more aquifers in one (1) day.
27 (3) Either:
28 (A) the facility is connected to existing pipeline facilities; or
29 (B) plans for the facility include the connection of the
30 facility to pipeline facilities;
31 through which at least five million (5,000,000) gallons of
32 ground water withdrawn by the well or wells to which
33 subdivision (1) refers could be transported in one (1) day to a
34 destination located at least twenty (20) miles from the well or
35 wells.
36 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "person" means any of the
37 following:
38 (1) An individual.
39 (2) A corporation, including a body corporate and politic
40 exercising public functions.
41 (3) A limited liability company, partnership, trust, or
42 unincorporated association.
2026 IN 1379—LS 6276/DI 150

7
1 (4) The state.
2 (5) A unit (as defined in IC 36-1-2-23).
3 (6) A board, a bureau, a commission, a division, a department,
4 an officer, an agency, an authority, or an instrumentality of
5 the state or of a unit.
6 (7) Two (2) or more of the persons identified in subdivisions
7 (1) through (6) acting in concert.
8 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "Wabash River basin" means the
9 area in:
10 (1) Tippecanoe County;
11 (2) Warren County;
12 (3) Vermillion County;
13 (4) Fountain County;
14 (5) Parke County; and
15 (6) Montgomery County;
16 that is drained by the Wabash River and the tributaries of the
17 Wabash River.
18 Sec. 6. Except as provided in sections 8, 9, and 10 of this chapter,
19 a person shall not establish a major ground water withdrawal
20 facility in the Wabash River basin during the period beginning
21 May 1, 2026, and ending June 30, 2028.
22 Sec. 7. Except as provided in section 9 of this chapter, no person
23 shall use state funding to plan the establishment of a major ground
24 water withdrawal facility in the Wabash River basin during the
25 period beginning May 1, 2026, and ending June 30, 2028.
26 Sec. 8. A county executive of a county located in the Wabash
27 River basin may adopt an order allowing a person to establish a
28 major ground water withdrawal facility in the county during the
29 period beginning May 1, 2026, and ending June 30, 2028. However,
30 if the proposed major ground water withdrawal facility will
31 withdraw water from or transport water through two (2) or more
32 counties, the county executive of each of these counties must adopt
33 an order allowing the establishment of a major ground water
34 withdrawal facility to proceed.
35 Sec. 9. The prohibitions in sections 6 and 7 of this chapter do not
36 apply to an operating ground water withdrawal facility that
37 increases its current:
38 (1) withdrawal; or
39 (2) pipeline;
40 capability by not more than two million (2,000,000) gallons of
41 ground water per day.
42 Sec. 10. The prohibitions in sections 6 and 7 of this chapter do
2026 IN 1379—LS 6276/DI 150

8
1 not apply to the establishment or planning of a major ground
2 water withdrawal facility in the Wabash River basin for which a
3 contract concerning the establishment or planning of the major
4 ground water withdrawal facility was entered into before January
5 1, 2026.
6 Sec. 11. This chapter expires July 1, 2029.
7 SECTION 8. An emergency is declared for this act.
